This is my Cheesy Chickpea Scramble 

• 🫘 2-4 Cups Chickpea Flour
• 🧂1/2- 1Tsp Indian Black Salt 
• 🧂Fresh Cracked Pepper
• 🌬1/3 Tsp Smoked Paprika
• 🧅1-2 Tsp Onion Powder 
• 🧄1-2 Tsp Fresh Garlic
• ✨️2-3Tb Nooch
• 🥛1-2 CupsOatmilk
• 🫒1Tb Olive Oil
• 🧈1-2Tb Vegan Butter
• 🧅1-2 Tbsp Finely Diced Onions
• 🌱Chives
• 🧀Vegan Cheese

Batter

- In a bowl 🥣 Whisk the Chickpea Flour, Oat Milk and your Seasonings/Spices together. 

- In a skillet warmed on Med/High heat, lightly Sautée Onions and Garlic in the oil. Just until fragrant

- To the skillet. Add Vegan Butter and let melt.

- Once melted. Pour your "egg" evenly into skillet

- Reduce Heat to Med/Low and Cover with lid.

- After about 3-5mins. Using a silicone spatula, Begin to gently "scramble" your mixture.

- Cover again and repeat process until desired doneness is obtained. 

- Sprinkle with vegan cheese, Chives, hot sauce etc... and ENJOY!

*Disclaimer...I don't measure, so please adjust to YOUR liking*

S/N: salt is optional! 
Add ANY and ALL Veggies of your choosing!

Ever since I hurt my back and was forced to sit my ass down for over a month and a half, I developed a #NewLove and #Appreciation for #Stretching. 
🙌🏽
My absolute favorite place to stretch is definitely in the #Sauna 
💪🏾🔥
Here are several reasons Why I stretch in the sauna...

• It increases the core temperature, which improves circulation
• Helps with meditation and stress relief.
• Causes sweating, which improves detoxification of my body. 
• Helps break down lactic acid, which causes pain and discomfort in muscles and joints.
• Helps with my flexibility and mobility. (I ain't no spring chicken, my body tends to stiffen up)
• Helps shed unnecessary fat 
🔥

‼️Things to Consider! ‼️

• Make sure the room is well ventilated. If the sauna is too hot or humid, it can be dangerous. This is why I don't necessarily like using the steam room... I'm a #SaunaGirl! 

• Drink plenty of water before and after your session. 💦

• Don't stay in the sauna for too long. Listen to your body and find the point of discomfort. 

• Avoid doing any strenuous yoga poses. The heat can make them more difficult to do, and you can risk injury. 

• Practice gentle stretching and relaxation poses. 
🔥

After I've finished my #SaunaStretch, I head straight to a cold shower. The cold shower removes toxins on the skin from sweating and drastically brings my body temperature. This further enhances the detoxification systems.
🚿

⚠️Disclaimer⚠️

This is what I DO! So as with ANYTHING, be sure to consult with your doctor before doing anything extreme or new! I'm not a professional, nor am I responsible for what you choose to do.

Cozy Blueberry & Peanut Butter Oats
🥰
• Old Fashioned Oats 🌾
• Plant Butter 🧈 
• Vanilla extract 
• Hemp Hearts ❤️
• Crunchy Peanut Butter 🥜 
• Blueberries 🫐 
• Walnuts 🌰
• Dates 🍬
• Maple Syrup 🍁 
• Pinch of pink Himalayan sea salt 
• Plant Milk
🥰
- Boil water add sea salt, vanilla, smashed date, and butter.
- Stir in oats...cook until desired doneness 
- Add plant milk to create a thinner consistency 
- Scoop a spoon full of peanut butter and place the spoon into a bowl.
- Pour hot oats over the spoon of peanut butter (helps it melt)
- Add your toppings! Mine are, Blueberries, Walnuts, Hemp Hearts and a drizzle of pure Maple Syrup!
🥰
Enjoy this Simple yet DELICIOUS bowl of happiness ANY TIME, not just for breakfast!

🥰
